values.description:
Getting the error ‘thread’ in namespace ‘std’ does not name a type private: std::thread rosQueueThread. Using boost works even if STL does not contain all C++11 features.

Also, setting the CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH would help avoid any build errors universally.

I've also noticed that the SetVelocityTarget() and setVelocityPID() does not work on Gazebo 2.2.6 but works fine on higher versions.
values.title: Getting the error ‘thread’ in namespace ‘std’ does not name a type private: std::thread rosQueueThread. Using boost works even if STL does not contain all C++11 features.

summary.raw:
Getting the error ‘thread’ in namespace ‘std’ does not name a type private: std::thread rosQueueThread. Using boost works even if STL does not contain all C++11 features.

Also, setting the CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH would help avoid any build errors universally.

I've also noticed that the SetVelocityTarget() and setVelocityPID() does not work on Gazebo 2.2.6 but works fine on higher versions.
summary.html:
Getting the error ‘thread’ in namespace ‘std’ does not name a type private: std::thread rosQueueThread. Using boost works even if STL does not contain all C++11 features.

Also, setting the CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH would help avoid any build errors universally.

I've also noticed that the SetVelocityTarget() and setVelocityPID() does not work on Gazebo 2.2.6 but works fine on higher versions.

values.description:
According to [changes coming to current gazebo default branch](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/), remove the `ENABLE_TESTS_COMPILATION` cmake parameter from the installation from source tutorial and add 'make tests' to compilation from source as an optional step.

I've removed the support for gazebo4 (deprecated) and create a copy of current tutorial for gazebo5,6,7.
values.title: Remove ENABLE_TESTS_COMPILATION from compiling from source

summary.raw:
According to [changes coming to current gazebo default branch](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/), remove the `ENABLE_TESTS_COMPILATION` cmake parameter from the installation from source tutorial and add 'make tests' to compilation from source as an optional step.

I've removed the support for gazebo4 (deprecated) and create a copy of current tutorial for gazebo5,6,7.
summary.html:
According to changes coming to current gazebo default branch, remove the ENABLE_TESTS_COMPILATION cmake parameter from the installation from source tutorial and add 'make tests' to compilation from source as an optional step.

I've removed the support for gazebo4 (deprecated) and create a copy of current tutorial for gazebo5,6,7.
